  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Natural Forest Protection</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims at developing a method to protect small-sized natural forests in Madagaskar, where fargmentation of the forests is a problem. In the pilot phase, the methods of conservation are forest restoration and creation of buffer zones by planting trees which provide food and wood for local people. This benefits also local agriculture and water resources, which promotes local participation in conservation. In the second phase, the purpose is to develop a forest monitoring system utilising remote sensing. In the future, the results can be applied in REDD projects for instance.</narrative>
  </description>
